adjectives.description: womanish (comparative more womanish, superlative most womanish)

entries.meaning: (often derogatory) Characteristic of a woman; effeminate, feminine. [from 14th c.]
examples: Friends are a comfort in misfortune, but one should not make them unhappy by seeking their sympathy, as is done by women and womanish men.

entries.meaning: Carried out by or pertaining to a woman. [from 14th c.]
